# Portfolio Webapp Coding Guidelines

## General Principles
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Prefer modern React patterns (hooks, async/await)
- Follow GitHub-inspired UI/UX principles: dark mode, clean hierarchy, high information density with readability
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use Framer Motion for smooth animations
- Use Lucide React for icons

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep components focused and reusable
- Use async/await over promises where possible
- Extract constants to separate files when appropriate

## UI/UX Guidelines (Inspired by GitHub)
- Dark mode as default (deep blue/navy background: #0d1117)
- Clear visual hierarchy with proper spacing
- Contextual information always visible (relative time displays)
- Smooth scroll animations with Framer Motion
- Responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Clean typography with clear hierarchy
- Use cards for project display with hover effects
- Maintain consistency in navigation and layout

## Component Structure
- Place reusable components in /components folder
- Use App Router structure (app directory)
- Separate data from components (data folder for project information)
- Use TypeScript interfaces for type safety

## Performance
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Use lazy loading where appropriate
- Minimize bundle size
- Use server components when possible

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML
- Include proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain proper color contrast

